Health department officials have temporarily closed a community healthcare centre in Inanda where six nurses tested positive for COVID-19. Courtesy #DStv403 DURBAN - A community healthcare centre in Inanda, north of Durban, has been temporarily closed after six nurses test positive for COVID-19. The KwaZulu Natal health department has advised community members to use nearby health facilities instead. READ: COVID-19: Retired nurses to the rescue The department says it's currently decontaminating the centre in Inanda's Newtown C section and it should be open again in about five days. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.